article.headline: Jacksonville 66, Kennesaw State 50
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. -- Delwan Graham had a double-double off the bench to lead Jacksonville over Kennesaw State 66-50 on Saturday night. The Dolphins (4-15, 2-6 Atlantic Sun Conference) scored 21 points off of 17 turnovers and held the Owls to just one 3-pointer (1 of 10). Jacksonville also outscored Kennesaw State 32-24 in the paint and outrebounded the owls 38-25. That led to 19 second-chance points. The Dolphins led 30-20 at halftime and opened up the second half on a 15-6 run to go up by 19 on Glenn Powell's jumper with 12:11 left. Aloys Cabell added 16 points for the Dolphins, who won their second in a row after losing 13 straight. Aaron Anderson tallied a double-double for Kennesaw State (3-17, 0-8) with 17 points and 11 rebounds and Markeith Cummings added 16 points. It was the eighth consecutive loss for the Owls.
